 daughter Sarah Hooker Wilson. The name traveled three generations to Alphonso's father before reaching him."}],"cross_connections":[{"type":"civic_peer","related_id":"HD1395","display_label":"Co-founded Skull and Bones at Yale in 1832 — both were Thomas Hooker descendants, though neither knew it.","link_text":"William Huntington Russell"},{"type":"civic_connection","related_id":"HD3711","display_label":"Ohio Republican Party founding-era figures — lawyer-jurist and newspaper editor.","link_text":"Edwin Cowles"}],"bio":{"display_name":"Alphonso Taft","first_name":"Alphonso","last_name":"Taft","married_names":[],"photo_url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/b/b9/Alphonso_Taft_-_cropped_and_retouched.jpg"},"residence":{},"baptism":{},"research_tags":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"institutions":[{"institution_id":"INST022","relationship":"founder","years":"1833"}],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"quotes":[],"military_service":[],"education":[{"institution_id":"INST022","dates":"1833","notes":" — Co-founder of Skull and Bones 1832 with William Huntington Russell. Father of President William Howard Taft. Hooker descendant."}],"slug":"alphonso-taft-1810"},"X01155":{"id":"X01155","has_descendants_documented":true,"classification":{"include_in_path_calculation":false,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":false,"descent_from_john_talcott":false,"is_thomas_descendant":false,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"tags":[],"sources":[{"label":"Wikipedia — Louise Taft","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Louise_Taft"}],"gender":"female","number_of_marriages":1,"marriages":[{"marriage_number":1,"spouse_id":"HD0337","children_ids":["HD3072","HD0338","HD3073","HD3074","HD3075"],"date_year":1853,"date_month":12,"date_day":26,"location_city":"Millbury","location_state":"Massachusetts"}],"parents":{},"notable":{"is_notable":true,"notable_category":["literature"],"notable_blurb":"Yale satirist; mother of President Taft","primary_url":